criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients diagnosed with Probable Alzheimer's Disease according to DSM-5 criteria;

          -  In the early stage of AD (MMSE from 20 to 25);

          -  Age from 60 - 80 years old;

          -  Received greater than 5 years of formal education

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with concomitant diseases (heart failure, kidney failure, liver failure or
             thyroid diseases) that affect cognitive functions;

          -  Diagnosed with other neuropsychological diseases (stroke, head trauma, depression,
             schizophrenia, sleep disordersâ€¦);

          -  Having major visual, auditory, reading or writing impairments;

          -  Patients and/or caregivers who decline to participate.
